---
const plants = [
  {
    name: "Honey Pie",
    status: "In progress",
    summary:
      "An orchid rescue being tracked through recovery, new growth, setbacks, and whatever lessons it decides to teach.",
  },
  {
    name: "Sun King",
    status: "Watching and learning",
    summary:
      "A bromeliad added to the plant journal as part of the broader rescue-and-care experiment.",
  },
];
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>Orchid Rescue | Brad Cooke</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A plant rescue journal tracking orchids, bromeliads, recovery notes, and lessons learned."
    />
  </head>

  <body>
    <main>
      <section>
        <h1>Orchid Rescue</h1>

        <p>
          I am not an orchid expert. This is a plant rescue journal about learning
          as I go, documenting what works, what fails, and what each plant teaches
          along the way.
        </p>

        <p>
          Some plants recover. Some do not. The point is to pay attention, keep
          notes, and see what a little patience can do.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Current Plants</h2>

        <div class="plant-grid">
          {plants.map((plant) => (
            <article class="plant-card">
              <h3>{plant.name}</h3>
              <p class="status">{plant.status}</p>
              <p>{plant.summary}</p>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Future Updates</h2>

        <p>
          This section can grow into individual plant pages, progress photos,
          bloom history, care notes, and before-and-after rescue timelines.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .plant-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .plant-card {
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .plant-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .status {
    font-weight: 700;
  }
</style>
